text.section:
Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Treasurer may invest or reinvest unexpended or surplus State money in obligations that the Maryland Environmental Service issues for a capital project if:
there is a commitment of federal funds for the project;
the Service has not received the federal funds;
the amount of the investment does not exceed the federal commitment; and
as to any investment or reinvestment that exceeds $500,000, the Board of Public Works approves the investment or reinvestment.
